article.headline: IPFW 68, S. Dakota St. 52
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) -- Jaraun Burrows scored 15 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead IPFW to a 68-52 victory over South Dakota State on Saturday. Tyler Best added 13 points and Demetrius Johnson came off the bench to score 12 points for the Mastodons (9-15). Kai Williams scored 19 points on 8-of-15 shooting to lead the Jackrabbits (5-19) in their fourth straight loss. Matt Cadwell added 13 points for South Dakota State. IPFW trailed 33-28 at halftime but went on a 14-2 run late in the second half to take a 13-point lead with 3:16 remaining. The Jackrabbits shot just 5-of-24 (20 percent) from the floor in the second half.
